1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:02,399
Welcome to the Accessibility First series.

2
00:00:02,399 --> 00:00:06,800
This is Guide 1: Foundations of Disability Inclusion and Accessible Design.

3
00:00:06,800 --> 00:00:14,000
Over the next 45 minutes, you will build the foundation for everything that follows in this 18-guide series.

4
00:00:14,000 --> 00:00:24,399
You will explore what disability means, examine the models that shape how we think about it, and learn a practical framework you can use starting today.

5
00:00:24,399 --> 00:00:28,799
At UHN, accessibility is not a checklist or a compliance exercise.

6
00:00:28,799 --> 00:00:40,799
It is a commitment to making sure every person who walks through our doors — as a patient, a visitor, or a colleague — can participate fully and with dignity.

7
00:00:40,799 --> 00:00:45,199
This guide is for everyone at UHN, regardless of your role.

8
00:00:45,199 --> 00:00:54,399
Whether you work at the bedside, at the front desk, in a lab, or in an office, accessibility is part of your practice.

9
00:00:54,399 --> 00:00:55,999
Let us get started.
